<topic class="popup" template="Popup" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="../../../helpproject.xsd">
  <title translate="true">Tip #50</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Heading3"><text styleclass="Heading3" translate="true">Tip of the Day</text></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><table rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="cell-padding:0px; cell-spacing:0px; border-width:0px; cell-border-width:0px;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:58px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="TipOfTheDayBulb.jpg" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td style="width:328px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">If you are using Dolphin on a system with limited screen real estate you can configure it to use the </text><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-style:italic;" translate="true">&apos;Basic class browser&apos;</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> view, which takes up much less space. Do &#160;this by changing the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Class Browser</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Class Name" translate="true">#defaultView</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> option &#160;(choose </text><text styleclass="Menu Command" translate="true">Tools/Options</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> with the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Class Browser</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> open). However, be aware that this view has much less functionality.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true">An alternative to re-configuring the default view is to unpin the filters pane in the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">Class Browser</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> and watch it slide away. With the </text><text styleclass="Program Feature" translate="true">System Browser</text><text styleclass="Normal" translate="true"> you can unpin both the filters and the packages panes which will give you much less clutter and plenty more screen space.</text><snippet src="Tip_Of_The_Day_Footer"/></para>
  </body>
</topic>
